CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1776957068
OL,3,CNew water saving labels 'waste of time
OL,4,Cand money', critics tell ITV News
OL,6,FOfficials have claimed that the labels
OL,7,Fcould help save #125 million on water
OL,8,Fbills and #147 million on energy bills
OL,9,Fover 10 years.
OL,11,FThey've suggested 1,200 million litres
OL,12,Fof water a day could be saved across
OL,13,Fthe UK - equivalent to 480 Olympic
OL,14,Fswimming pools.
OL,16,FBy encouraging consumers to choose a
OL,17,Fdevice labelled as highly water
OL,18,Fefficient, it's hoped households will
OL,19,Fsee decreased bills through water
OL,20,Fsavings - and subsequent energy
OL,21,Fsavings related to hot water use.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1776957068
OL,3,CNew water saving labels 'waste of time
OL,4,Cand money', critics tell ITV News
OL,6,F"25% of total water consumption in the
OL,7,Fhousehold is down to showering," Paul
OL,8,FRavnbo-West, a shower expert at the
OL,9,FTriton factory in Nuneaton said, "So
OL,10,Fif a family of four can save around
OL,11,Fabout 55,000 litres of water, that's
OL,12,Fabout #132 in Water and Energy bills
OL,13,Fper year."
OL,15,FThe government has backing from a
OL,16,Frange of consumer and trade bodies and
OL,17,Fsays the new labels will start to
OL,18,Fappear this autumn.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@JO]
